        "body": "So I was given this assignment to simply convert infix math expressions to postfix expressions. For example: a+b+c converts to ab+c+. However, I am having trouble implementing the logic provided by my professor (as I am a novice in programming), which is as follows: \n\n\nVariables (such as a, b, and c) are directly copied to the output.\nLeft parentheses are always pushed onto a stack.\nWhen a right parenthesis is encountered, the symbol on the top of the stack is popped off the\nstack and copied to the output. This process repeats until the top of the stack is a left\nparenthesis. When that occurs, both parentheses are discarded.\nIf the symbol been scanned has a higher precedence than the symbol on the top of the stack,\nthe symbol being scanned is pushed onto the stack.\nIf the symbol been scanned has a lower or the same precedence than the symbol at the top of\nthe stack, the symbol at the top of the stack is popped off to the output. The symbol been\nscanned will be compared with the new top element on the stack, and the process continues.\nWhen the input is empty, the stack is popped to the output until the stack is empty. Then the\nalgorithm terminates.\nIf the input is empty but the stack still has a left parenthesis, or a right parenthesis is scanned\nwhen the stack is empty, the parenthesis of the original expression were unbalanced.\n\n\nAnd here is my code and the results so far for this assignment using a char[] stack. I tried to implement the above bullet points in the &quot;ExprConverter&quot; class under the &quot;toPostfix&quot; method, but I&#39;m fairly certain I did not do it correctly and this is the root of the problem, as I am getting incorrect output. \n\nStack Class:\n\n\n\nConverter Class: \n\n\n\nDriver Class:\n\n\n\nDriver Class Results:\n\n\n\nSo if anyone could help figure out what I am doing wrong, I would really appreciate it!\n",
        "excerpt": "];\n}\n\npublic char peek()\n{\n    if(top == 0)\n        throw new <span class=\"highlight\">RuntimeException</span>(&quot;Stack is empty.&quot;);\n\n    return arrayStack[top - 1];\n}\n\npublic boolean isEmpty()\n{\n    return top == 0;\n}\n\npublic int size &hellip;  static void main(String[] args) \n{\n    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(&quot;a+b+c&quot;);\n    System.out.println(sb);\n    ExprConverter <span class=\"highlight\">test</span> = new ExprConverter(&quot;a+b+c&quot;);\n}\n}\n\n\nDriver Class Results:\n\na+b+c\nab+c\n[+]\n\n\nSo if anyone could help figure out what I am doing wrong, I would really appreciate it!\n &hellip; ",
