        "body": "Check the Java API for List. The get(int) method is declared to throw only the IndexOutOfBoundException which extends RuntimeException. You are trying to tell Mockito to a throw an exception that is not valid to be thrown by that particular method call.\n\nTo clarify further. The List interface does not provide for a checked Exception to be thrown from the get() method and that is why Mockito is failing. When you create the mocked List, Mockito using the definition of List.class to creates its mock. The behavior you are specifying with the  doesn&#39;t match the method signature in List.class, so Mockito fails. If you really want to do this, then have Mockito throw a  or even better throw a  since the API specifies that that is the only valid Exception to be thrown.\n",
